    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="519"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6101</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SSCA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear <persName corresp="#p_SSCA1">Sir Cecil</persName>
                    </hi>: Referring to the paraphrase of a telegram from London which you left with
                    Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PW1">Phillips</persName> on Saturday afternoon, July
                    28, regarding a conference of shipping representatives of Allied countries soon
                    to be held in London in order to discuss the whole shipping problem, I beg to
                    say that it has been decided that inasmuch as there is a conference on shipping
                    being held here now it would be well for this Government to await the result of
                    this conference before taking part in the conference suggested in London.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
